n instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret FitzRobert was born in 1140, in Newbold on Avon, Warwickshire, England. She married Robert fitzWaltheof. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1210, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1140–1210":"1140–1210","1155–1190":"1155–1190","1130–1165":"1130–1165","1170–1206":"1170–1206","1206":"1206","1190":"1190","about 1170":"umbes 1170","after 1190":"pärast 1190","1210":"1210","1155":"1155","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","Stockport, Cheshire, England":"Stockport, Cheshire, England","Stockport, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Stockport, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Newbold on Avon, Warwickshire, England":"Newbold on Avon, Warwickshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1140–1210":"1140–1210","1155–1190":"1155–1190","1130–1165":"1130–1165","1170–1206":"1170–1206","1206":"1206","1190":"1190","about 1170":"noin 1170","after 1190":"1190 jälkeen","1210":"1210","1155":"1155","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","Stockport, Cheshire, England":"Stockport, Cheshire, England","Stockport, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Stockport, Cheshire, Englanti